    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nTried enabling UI2 following the news - with `require('vim._core.ui2').enable()`, but it did not work:\n\n```\nE5108: Lua: vim/_core/shared.lua:0: after the second argument: expected table, got nil\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'error'\n        vim/_core/shared.lua: in function 'validate'\n        vim/_core/shared.lua: in function 'tbl_deep_extend'\n        vim/_core/ui2.lua: in function 'enable'\n        [string \":lua\"]:1: in main chunk\n```\n\nFix requires passing an empty table: `require('vim._core.ui2').enable({})`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean -c \"lua require('vim._core.ui2').enable()\"\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExpecting news to provide working code samples.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1774638290\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nMacOS 26.4 (25E246)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nHomebrew",
