        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This tripped me up a few times before since this is the only place in the LUA API that does not accept `nil` in place of an empty table (not counting the exposed Nvim API `vim.api.*`, where this is different due to the different clients.)\n\nAs this would be a one-line change and not lock us into anything (since the whole module is marked as temporary), I vote for just supporting `enable()` for `enable({})` (which should remain supported).",
